{0 Go to definition}

Jump from a link to its definition target within an Oystermark vault.

{1 Input}

A cursor position (0-based line and character) in a markdown file that
belongs to a vault with a built index.

{1:link_detection Link detection}

The cursor must fall within the byte range of a recognized link form:

{ul
  {- {b Wikilinks}: [[[target]]], [[[target#heading]]],
     [[[target#^blockid]]], [![[embed]]]}
  {- {b Markdown links}: [[text](target)]}
  {- {b Markdown images}: [![alt](img.png)]}
}

External URLs ([https://...], [http://...]) are {e not} recognized as
navigable links and produce no result.

{1:resolution Resolution}

Once a link is detected, it is resolved against the vault index via
{!Oystermark.Vault.Resolve.resolve}.  The resolution cases and their
results are:

{t
  | Link form                 | Target path       | Target line              |
  |---------------------------|-------------------|--------------------------|
  | [[[note]]]                | resolved file     | 0 (top of file)          |
  | [[text](note)]            | resolved file     | 0                        |
  | [![[file.png]]]           | resolved file     | 0                        |
  | [[[note#Heading]]]        | resolved file     | line of matching heading |
  | [[[note#^blockid]]]       | resolved file     | line of matching block   |
  | [[[#Heading]]]            | current file      | line of heading          |
  | [[[#^blockid]]]           | current file      | line of block            |
  | unresolved link           | {e None}          | —                        |
}

{2 Heading lookup}

Headings are matched by {e slug}: the heading text is slugified (e.g.
"Section One" becomes [section-one]) and compared against the fragment.
The line number is read from the heading AST node's [Cmarkit.Textloc]
metadata.

{2 Block-ID lookup}

Block IDs ([^id] suffix on a paragraph) are matched by exact string
comparison on the ID.  The line number is read from the paragraph AST
node's [Cmarkit.Textloc] metadata.

{2 Fallback}

If the target heading or block ID is not found in the target file, or the
target file cannot be read, the result falls back to line 0.

{1:edge_cases Edge cases}

{ul
  {- {b Cursor outside any link}: no result.}
  {- {b Character offset past end of line}: clamped to content length.}
  {- {b Line past end of content}: clamped to end of content.}
}

{1 Multi-target ambiguity}

When {!Oystermark.Vault.Resolve.resolve} returns multiple candidates,
go-to-definition picks the first candidate (per vault resolution order).

{1 Embed links}

Embed links ([![[note]]]) are treated identically to regular wikilinks
for navigation: the target is the embedded file at line 0.  No distinct
behavior (e.g. inline preview) is provided by this feature.

{1 Assumptions and limitations}

{ul
  {- Position encoding: see {!page-"feature-utf16-positions"}.}
  {- The document is re-parsed on every request (no caching).}
}
